note: Former shelfmark: MS X893.7 K84 I113.

supportDesc.extent: i, 300, i leaves : 166 x 116 (106 x 59) mm, bound to 167 x 123 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Page numbers in Hindu-Arabic numerals in pencil, upper outer corners (iii, 2-590, ix).

layoutDesc.layout: 15 long lines; catchwords every verso, lower left; border-ruled.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, vocalized.

decoNote: Polychrome and gold illuminated double-page opening (p. unnumbered verso-[1]r); polychrome and gold floral marginal medallions; gold roundels with orange and blue dots mark verse endings; textblock border-ruled in red and gold; sūrah headings in white on gold background; readings and verse counts in red.

binding.p: Red leather with fore-edge flap (Type II); gilt-stamped central mandorla and cornerpiece onlays; gold-tooled frame and pendants on the vertical axis; spine and edges repaired.

origin.p: Copy completed in 1227 AH. (1812 or 1813 CE) by al-Sayyid Ḥāfiẓ Ibrāhīm ibn al-Sayyid Muṣṭafá (p. [598]).

history.provenance: Presumed to be a gift of David Eugene Smith, 1931-1934.
